problem_text: Quadrilateral A B C D is a rhombus. If m \angle A B C = 2 x - 7 and m \angle B C D = 2 x + 3, find m \angle D A B.
compact_text: Quadrilateral ABCD is a rhombus. If m \angle ABC = 2x-7 and m \angle BCD = 2x+3, find m \angle DAB.
annotat_text: Quadrilateral ABCD is a rhombus. If $m\angle ABC = 2x – 7$ and $m\angle BCD = 2x + 3$, find $m\angle DAB$.
